\h Ezra
\toc1 Ezra
\toc2 Ezra
\toc3 Ezra
\mt1 Ezra
\is1 Introduction
\ip \bk The account of Ezra\bk*, is like a continuation of \bk The Chronicles\bk*вҖ”it tells us about the returning home of other Jews who had been taken to Babylon as captives, and the restoration of daily life in Yerushalem (Jerusalem) and of worshipping at the temple.
\ip It's divided into three main sections: 1. The declaration of King Koresh (Cyrus) of Persia (Heb. Paras) to allow a group of exiled Jews to return to Yerushalem from Babylon. 2. The rebuilding of the temple and its dedication, and the return to worshipping Yahweh there in Yerushalem. 3. The return of a different group of Jewish descendants to Yerushalem under the leadership of EzraвҖ”the one knowledgable about God's instructions. He assisted the Israelis to return to their beliefs and customs, so that their worshipping of the true God wouldn't be forgotten.
\iot Main components of this account
\io1 The first group of exiled Jews return home \ior 1:1вҖ“2:70\ior*
\io1 The rebuilding of the temple and its dedication \ior 3:1вҖ“6:22\ior*
\io1 Ezra leads other exiles to return to Yehudah (Judah) \ior 7:1вҖ“10:44\ior*
\rem This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the Open English Translation of the Bible. Please double-check the text in advance before using in public.
\ie
\c 1
\s1 Koresh returns some Jews
\rem /s1 Return of exiles to Jerusalem; Cyrus Helps the Exiles to Return; End of the Babylonian Captivity; Cyrus Commands the Jews to Return; Cyrus Allows the Exiles to Return
\p
\v 1 In the first year that Koresh \add (CyrusВҰ217150)\add* was king of PersiaВҰ217138 \add (Heb. Paras)\add*, YahwehВҰ217142 stirredВҰ217145 up \add *his\add* spiritВҰ217149 in orderВҰ217139 to fulfilВҰ217139 what \add *he'd\add* spoken through the prophet Yirmeyah \add (Jeremiah)\add*.\x + \xo 1:1: \xt Jer 25:11; 29:10.\x* \add вүҲSoВҰ217134\add* \add @the king\add* distributed a written proclamationВҰ217156 throughout his kingdomВҰ217159, saying,
\v 2 вҖңKoreshВҰ217167, kingВҰ217168 of PersiaВҰ217169, declares this: YahwehВҰ217175, the godВҰ217176 of heavenВҰ217177, has givenВҰ217173 me all the kingdomsВҰ217171 in the world, and he's appointedВҰ217180 me to buildВҰ217182 a residence for him in YerushalemВҰ217186 in YehudahВҰ217188.\x + \xo 1:2: \xt Isa 44:28.\x*
\v 3 Anyone among you who's one of his followers is free to go to Yerushalem (in YehudahВҰ217202) \add to help\add* buildВҰ217203 a temple there for Yisrael'sВҰ217209 god YahwehВҰ217207вҖ”the god of Yerushalem. May GodВҰ217197 go with you.
\v 4 Those who live near these peopleВҰ217227 but who are not going themselves, should donate goldВҰ217230 and silverВҰ217229, and goodsВҰ217231 and livestockВҰ217232, plus cash as a voluntary offeringВҰ217235 for God's temple in YerushalemВҰ217239.
\p
\v 5 ThenВҰ217241 \add some\add* of the leaders of BenyaminВҰ217245 and YehudahВҰ217244, and \add some\add* priestsВҰ217246 and LevitesВҰ217247вҖ”all of whom had had their spirits stirredВҰ217249 up by GodВҰ217250вҖ”left to goВҰ217254 and build Yahweh'sВҰ217259 residence in YerushalemВҰ217261.
\v 6 TheirВҰ217267 neighboursВҰ217265 had helped them by \add вүҲdonating\add* goldВҰ217271 and silverВҰ217270 utensils, goodsВҰ217272 and livestock, and expensive giftsВҰ217274, as well as the voluntary offeringsВҰ217280 of cash.
\p
\v 7 Then King Koresh brought out the equipment from Yahweh's temple thatВҰ217292 NevukadnetstsarВҰ217294 \add (Nebuchadnezzar)\add* had brought \add all the way\add* from YerushalemВҰ217295 and had put in the house of his gods.
\v 8 \add *He\add* \add вүҲput the treasurerВҰ217310 Mitedat in charge of bringing them out\add* and Sheshbatstsar, the ruler of YehudahВҰ217314, \add вүҲin charge of accepting them and listing them\add*.
\v 9 There were: thirtyВҰ217320 goldВҰ217319 basins, one thousandВҰ217324 silverВҰ217323 basins, twenty-nine knivesВҰ217325,
\v 10 thirtyВҰ217332 goldВҰ217331 bowls, 410 silverВҰ217334 bowls, and a thousandВҰ217341 otherВҰ217340 utensils,
\v 11 \add вүҲcoming to a total of 5,400 goldВҰ217347 and silverВҰ217348 utensils\add*. SheshbatstsarВҰ217355 \add вүҲtook all of that with the group\add* of exilesВҰ217358 going from BabylonВҰ217359 to YerushalemВҰ217360.
\c 2
\s1 The list of returning exiles
\rem /s1 The List of Those Who Returned from Exile; The List of the Exiles Who Returned; Exiles Who Returned with Zerubbabel; List of the Returned Exiles
\r (Neh. 7:4-73)
\p
\v 1 Out of the captivesВҰ217368 that Babylonian King NevukadnetstsarВҰ217372 \add (Nebuchadnezzar)\add* had brought \add as slaves\add* to BabylonВҰ217376, theseВҰ217363 are \add their descendants\add* who returned to YerushalemВҰ217379 in YehudahвҖ”\add вүҲeach person returning to their own ancestral townВҰ217382\add*.
\v 2 The ones who wentВҰ217386 with ZerubabelВҰ217389 were: YeshuaВҰ217390, NehemyahВҰ217391, SerayahВҰ217392, Re'elayah, MordecaiВҰ217394, BilshanВҰ217395, MisparВҰ217396, BigvaiВҰ217397, RehumВҰ217398, and Ba'anah.
\p Their numbersВҰ217400 were:
\li1
\v 3 2,172 descendantsВҰ217406 of FaroshВҰ217407,
\li1
\v 4 372 descendantsВҰ217414 of ShefatyahВҰ217415,
\li1
\v 5 775 descendantsВҰ217422 of ArahВҰ217423,
\li1
\v 6 2,812 descendants of FahatВҰ217432-MoabВҰ217433, from the families of YeshuaВҰ217435 and YoabВҰ217436,
\li1
\v 7 1,254 descendantsВҰ217444 of ElamВҰ217445,
\li1
\v 8 945 descendantsВҰ217452 of ZattuВҰ217453,
\li1
\v 9 760 descendantsВҰ217460 of ZakkaiВҰ217461,
\li1
