\v 26 621 from RamahВҰ217589 and GevaВҰ217590,
\li1
\v 27 122 from MikmasВҰ217598,
\li1
\v 28 223 from Beyt-El and AiВҰ217608,
\li1
\v 29 52 from NevoВҰ217615,
\li1
\v 30 156 from MagbishВҰ217621,
\li1
\v 31 1,254 from the otherВҰ217629 ElamВҰ217628,
\li1
\v 32 320 from HarimВҰ217637,
\li1
\v 33 725 from LodВҰ217645, HadidВҰ217646, and OnoВҰ217647,
\li1
\v 34 345 from YerichoВҰ217655,
\li1
\v 35 3,630 from SenaahВҰ217663.
\p
\v 36 The priestsВҰ217671 \add who returned\add*:
\li1 973 descendants of YedaiahВҰ217673 (descendants of YeshuaВҰ217675),
\li1
\v 37 1,052 descendantsВҰ217682 of ImmerВҰ217683,
\li1
\v 38 1,247 descendantsВҰ217689 of FashhurВҰ217690,
\li1
\v 39 1,017 descendantsВҰ217697 of HarimВҰ217698.
\p
\v 40 The LevitesВҰ217704 \add who returned\add*:
\li1 74 descendants of YeshuaВҰ217707 and KadmielВҰ217708, who were from the family of HodavyahВҰ217710,
\li1
\v 41 128 musicians who were descendantsВҰ217716 of AsafВҰ217717,
\li1
\v 42 139 gatekeepers who were descendants of the gatekeepers ShallumВҰ217727, AterВҰ217730, TalmonВҰ217733, AkkubВҰ217736, HatitaВҰ217738, andВҰ217744 ShobaiВҰ217740,
\p
\v 43 The templeВҰ217747 servantsВҰ217747 \add who returned\add*:
\li1 The descendants of ZihaВҰ217750, HasufaВҰ217753, and TabaotВҰ217755,
\li1
\v 44 the descendants of KerosВҰ217759, SiahaВҰ217762, and FadonВҰ217764,
\li1
\v 45 the descendants of Levanah, Hagavah, and Akkuv,
\li1
\v 46 the descendants of HagavВҰ217777, ShalmaiВҰ217780, and HananВҰ217783,
\li1
\v 47 the descendants of GiddelВҰ217787, GaharВҰ217790, and ReayahВҰ217792,
\li1
\v 48 the descendants of RetsinВҰ217796, NekodaВҰ217799, and GazzamВҰ217801,
\li1
\v 49 the descendants of Uzza, Faseah, and BesaiВҰ217810,
\li1
\v 50 the descendants of Asnah, Me'unim, and Nefusim,
\li1
\v 51 the descendants of BakbukВҰ217825, HakufaВҰ217828, and HarhurВҰ217830,
\li1
\v 52 the descendants of BazlutВҰ217834, MehidaВҰ217837, and HarshaВҰ217839,
\li1
\v 53 the descendants of BarkosВҰ217843, SiseraВҰ217846, and TemahВҰ217849,
\li1
\v 54 and the descendants of Netsiyah and Atifa.
\p
\v 55 The descendants of Shelomoh's \add (Solomon'sВҰ217858)\add* servantsВҰ217857 \add who returned\add*:
\li1 the descendants SotaiВҰ217861, Hassoferet, PerudaВҰ217866,
\li1
\v 56 the descendants of YaalahВҰ217870, DarkonВҰ217873, and GiddelВҰ217875,
\li1
\v 57 the descendants of Shefatyah, HattilВҰ217881, PokeretВҰ217883 Hatstsebayim, and AmiВҰ217886.
\m
\v 58 \add Altogether\add* there were 392 descendants of templeВҰ217890 workers and Shelomoh's servants \add who returned\add*.
\p
\v 59 \add вүҲAnother group\add* wentВҰ217901 from \add the towns of\add* Tel-Melah, Tel-HarshaВҰ217905, Keruv, AddonВҰ217907, and ImmerВҰ217908, \add вүҲbut\add* they \add вүҲdidn'tВҰ217909 know their ancestry\add* \add from before they were taken as captives\add*.
\p
\v 60 There were 652 people who were descendants of DelayahВҰ217922, Toviyyah, andВҰ217931 NekodaВҰ217927,
\v 61 and from the sons of the priestsВҰ217935: the descendants of Havayyah; the descendants of HakkotsВҰ217939; and the descendants of Barzillai, who took a wifeВҰ217947 from the daughtersВҰ217944 of Barzillai the GileaditeВҰ217946, so he was calledВҰ217948 by theirВҰ217951 nameВҰ217951.
\v 62 \add *They\add* had searched for their \add #records\add* among the \add вүҲgenealogiesВҰ217956\add*, but \add вүҲcouldn't find\add* \add their families listed\add*, \add вүҲso\add* they were \add вүҲdisqualified to serve as priestsВҰ217962\add*.
\v 63 \add вүҲAlso\add* the governorВҰ217965 told them that theyВҰ217970 mustn't eatВҰ217970 any of the holiest food untilВҰ217973 a priestВҰ217975 \add вүҲcould use the Urim andВҰ217977 Thummim\add* \add to determine their status\add*.\x + \xo 2:63: \xt Num 27:21.\x*
\p
\v 64 \add вүҲAltogether in this group\add*, 42,360 people \add returned to Yehudah\add*.
\v 65 \add вүҲnot counting\add* theirВҰ217992 7,337 male and female servants, plus 200 male and female musicians.
\v 66 \add They also took\add* 736 horses and 245 mulesВҰ218011,
\v 67 435 camels and 6,720 donkeysВҰ218021.
\p
\v 68 When some of the \add вүҲheadsВҰ218029 of familiesВҰ218030\add* got to Yahweh's temple in YerushalemВҰ218035, they freely donated \add вүҲso thatВҰ218034 itВҰ218039 could be rebuilt\add*.
\v 69 They each donated to the treasuryВҰ218046 according to \add вүҲtheirВҰ218044 individual resources\add*вҖ”\add a total of\add* sixty-one thousand goldВҰ218048 coins, fiveВҰ218057 thousand silverВҰ218055 bars, and a hundredВҰ218061 sets of clothing for the priestsВҰ218060.
\p
\v 70 \add вүҲSo\add* the priestsВҰ218065 and the LevitesВҰ218066, and some of the peopleВҰ218069, and the singersВҰ218070, and the gatekeepersВҰ218071 and the templeВҰ218072 servantsВҰ218072 \add returned to\add* live in their \add ancestral\add* cities, and \add so\add* all the Israeli cities \add вүҲhad returnees living in them\add*.\x + \xo 2:70: \xt 1Ch 9:2; Neh 11:3.\x*
\c 3
\s1 Rebuilding the altar
\rem /s1 The Altar Is Rebuilt; Worship Begins Again; Rebuilding the Altar; Worship Restored at Jerusalem; Restoration of altar and temple
\p
\v 1 In the seventhВҰ218082 monthВҰ218081, the IsraelisВҰ218084 from their \add various\add* cities, gatheredВҰ218087 together \add вүҲin unity\add* in YerushalemВҰ218093.
\v 2 Then Yotsadak's son YeshuaВҰ218097 and his brothers the priestsВҰ218102, and Shealti'el'sВҰ218106 son ZerubavelВҰ218103 and his brothers, and they built the altarВҰ218111 to offer up burntВҰ218116 offerings to Yisrael'sВҰ218113 god on it as is writtenВҰ218117 in the law of MoshehВҰ218119, the man of GodВҰ218112.\x + \xo 3:2: \xt Exo 27:1.\x*
\v 3 They set the altarВҰ218125 up on its foundationВҰ218128 becauseВҰ218132 they were worried \add about trouble from\add* some of the \add other\add* peopleВҰ218132 groups \add вүҲin the region\add*. ThenВҰ218124 they offered burnt offerings to YahwehВҰ218139 on it \add as well as the regular\add* morningВҰ218141 andВҰ218124 eveningВҰ218142 burnt offerings.\x + \xo 3:3: \xt Num 28:1-8.\x*
\v 4 ThenВҰ218144 theyВҰ218144 observed the Celebration in Shelters as \add вүҲper the writtenВҰ218149 instructions\add*\x + \xo 3:4: \xt Num 29:12-38.\x* with a burntВҰ218150 offeringВҰ218150 each day as required.
\v 5 After that \add was over\add*, they kept up the regular burntВҰ218163 offerings, plus those for the new moons andВҰ218160 other timesВҰ218168 that Yahweh required, as well as any free-will offerings to Yahweh.\x + \xo 3:5: \xt Num 28:11вҖ“29:39.\x*
\v 6 \add вүҲEven though the templeВҰ218184 foundationВҰ218187 rebuilding hadn't started yet\add*, the people started sacrificing burntВҰ218182 offeringsВҰ218181 to YahwehВҰ218183 \add вүҲfrom the beginning of October\add*.
\s1 Rebuilding the temple
\rem /s1 Rebuilding the Temple; The Rebuilding of the Temple Begins; The People Rebuild the Temple
\p
\v 7 They donated cash to the stone-workers and carpentersВҰ218193, and food, drinkВҰ218195, and oil to the workers from Tsidon \add (Sidon)\add* and Tsor \add (TyreВҰ218198)\add* to \add вүҲfloat\add* cedarВҰ218201 \add logs along the coast\add* from Lebananon into Port Yafo \add (Joppa)\add* with the permission of Persian King Koresh \add (CyrusВҰ218210)\add*.
\rem /s1 Foundation Laid for the Temple
\p
\v 8 In the second monthВҰ218225 of second yearВҰ218217 \add вүҲsince their return to\add* Yerushalem, Shealtiel'sВҰ218231 son Zerubavel and Yotsadak's son YeshuaВҰ218232, and the rest of their brothersВҰ218237 the priestsВҰ218239 and the Levites, and \add вүҲeveryone except who'd returned\add* to Yerushalem from captivityВҰ218244, beganВҰ218227 work on God's residence, and theyВҰ218227 appointedВҰ218246 the Levites who were twentyВҰ218251 and over to act as overseers for the work of \add rebuilding\add* Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple\add*.
\v 9 \add вүҲAndВҰ218279\add* YeshuaВҰ218264 with his brothers and their sons, KadmielВҰ218267 and his sons, (all descendants of YehudahВҰ218271) \add вүҲcooperated\add* to act as overseers for those doing the work at the \add вүҲtemple\add* \add together with\add* Henadad'sВҰ218282 sons \add вүҲand grandsons\add*, and their brothers the LevitesВҰ218285.
\p
\v 10 \add вүҲWhen the buildersВҰ218288 had\add* laid the foundationВҰ218287 of Yahweh's templeВҰ218291, they \add вүҲgot\add* the priestsВҰ218294 \add вүҲto stand there in their robes\add* with their trumpetsВҰ218296, andВҰ218287 Asaf'sВҰ218300 descendants (who were LevitesВҰ218297) with their cymbalsВҰ218301, to praiseВҰ218302 Yahweh \add вүҲusing the rhythms composed by\add* DavidВҰ218309, the \add former\add* IsraeliВҰ218310 kingВҰ218310.\x + \xo 3:10: \xt 1Ch 25:1.\x*
\v 11 Then they sang in responseвҖ”praisingВҰ218315 andВҰ218314 thankingВҰ218316 Yahweh: вҖң\add вүҲYes,\add* he is goodВҰ218319, because his loyal commitment to YisraelВҰ218326 \add вүҲwill continue forever\add*.вҖқ
\p Then all the peopleВҰ218329 shouted a greatВҰ218333 shout in praiseВҰ218334 to Yahweh because the foundationВҰ218337 of Yahweh's \add temple\add* had been laid.\x + \xo 3:11: \xt 1Ch 16:34; 2Ch 5:13; 7:3; Psa 100:5; 106:1; 107:1; 118:1; 136:1; Jer 33:11.\x*
\v 12 Many of the olderВҰ218348 priestsВҰ218344 and LevitesВҰ218345, and \add вүҲclan leaders\add* who'd seenВҰ218350 the firstВҰ218354 \add вүҲtemple\add*, wept loudly \add вүҲwhen they witnessed\add* the foundingВҰ218355 of this \add *one\add*, \add вүҲbut others were shoutingВҰ218363 happily with loud voices\add*.
\v 13 SoВҰ218368 the people couldn't differentiate the happy sounds from the sound of the people weepingВҰ218375, because the people were shoutingВҰ218379 \add вүҲvery loudly andВҰ218368 it could be heardВҰ218383 from far away\add*.
\c 4
\s1 Opposition to rebuilding the temple
\rem /s1 Opposition to the Rebuilding; Opposition to the Rebuilding of the Temple; Enemies Oppose the Rebuilding; Resistance to Rebuilding the Temple
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲNow\add* the enemies of YehudahВҰ218391 and BenyaminВҰ218392 heardВҰ218389 that the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ218400 who'd come back from\add* exileВҰ218396 were buildingВҰ218397 a templeВҰ218398 for Yisrael'sВҰ218401 godВҰ218400 YahwehВҰ218399.
\v 2 \add вүҲso\add* they went to Zerubavel and to the \add other\add* \add вүҲclan leaders\add* and they saidВҰ218411 to them, вҖңLet us \add вүҲhelp you with the buildingВҰ218413 work\add*, because like you, we \add вүҲworship\add* your godВҰ218418 and we've been sacrificingВҰ218423 to him sinceВҰ218424 the daysВҰ218424 of the Assyrian kingВҰ218427 Esar-HaddonвҖ”the one who \add вүҲsent\add* us here.вҖқ\x + \xo 4:2: \xt 2Ki 17:24-41.\x*
\p
\v 3 \add вүҲButВҰ218433\add* Zerubavel, and YeshuaВҰ218436, and the rest of the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ218440 clan leaders\add* saidВҰ218433 to them, вҖңIt's not for youВҰ218443 and for us to build a houseВҰ218446 for our god, but we ourselves togetherВҰ218450 will build for Yisrael'sВҰ218440 godВҰ218447 YahwehВҰ218452, just as the Persian King Koresh \add (CyrusВҰ218458)\add* has commandedВҰ218456 us.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 \add вүҲThose local\add* people had been discouraging the people of YehudahВҰ218471 andВҰ218463 trying to stop them from buildingВҰ218475.
\v 5 They'd \add also\add* hired \add вүҲinfluencers to work againstВҰ218478 them throughout the reignsВҰ218490\add* of the Persian kings Koresh \add (CyrusВҰ218485)\add* andВҰ218488 Dareyavesh \add (DariusВҰ218491)\add*.
\s1 The opposition of replacement of Yerushalem
\rem /s1 Rebuilding of Jerusalem Opposed; Later Opposition Under Xerxes and Artaxerxes; Later Opposition under King Artaxerxes; Opposition to the Rebuilding of Jerusalem
\p
\v 6 Now at the beginningВҰ218498 of the reignВҰ218496 of Ahashverosh \add (AhasuerusВҰ218497 or Xerxes)\add*, theyВҰ218500 \add вүҲforwarded\add* an accusationВҰ218501 against those who lived in YerushalemВҰ218506 andВҰ218506 \add throughout\add* YehudahВҰ218505.
\p
\v 7 And in the daysВҰ218509 of Persian King Artahshasta \add (ArtaxerxesВҰ218510)\add*, BishlamВҰ218512, MitredatВҰ218513, Taveel and the rest of \add #their\add* companions wroteВҰ218511 to the kingВҰ218522. (The letter was writtenВҰ218527 in AramaicВҰ218528 \add (Syrian)\add* and \add вүҲusing that alphabet\add*).
\p
\v 8 RehumВҰ218533 \add вүҲthe high commissioner\add* and ShimshaiВҰ218537 the \add вүҲprovincial secretary\add* wroteВҰ218539 a letterВҰ218540 to King Artahshasta against YerushalemВҰ218544 as followsВҰ218547:
\p
\v 9 \add From\add* RehumВҰ218550 \add вүҲthe high commissioner\add* and ShimshaiВҰ218554 the \add вүҲprovincial secretary\add*, and the \add вүҲour\add* companions, the judges and the rulers, the officialsВҰ218561, the Persians, the Erechites, the Babylonians, the Susaites (that is, the Elamites),
\v 10 and the rest of the nations thatВҰ218573 the famous and powerful \add King\add* Asenappar exiledВҰ218574 \add from other nations\add* and \add вүҲforced\add* them to live in the citiesВҰ218580 of ShomronВҰ218582 \add (Samaria)\add*, and the \add вүҲprovince went of the Euphrates riverВҰ218586\add*.
\p And now
\v 11 this is \add вүҲwhat the letterВҰ218591 said\add* thatВҰ218592 theyВҰ218593 sentВҰ218593 to himВҰ218594:
\p To Artahshasta \add (ArtaxerxesВҰ218597)\add* the kingВҰ218598 \add from\add* yourВҰ218599 servantsВҰ218599 \add вүҲon this side of\add* the riverВҰ218605.
\p And now
\v 12 let itВҰ218610 be knownВҰ218609 to the kingВҰ218611 that the Jews who \add вүҲleft your region\add* have comeВҰ218620 to us at YerushalemВҰ218621 \add вүҲto\add* rebuild that rebelliousВҰ218623 and evil cityВҰ218622вҖ”they're \add currently\add* finishingВҰ218630 the wallsВҰ218628 and repairingВҰ218633 the \add buildingВҰ218627\add* foundationsВҰ218632.
\v 13 Now let it be knownВҰ218636 to the kingВҰ218638 that if that cityВҰ218641 is builtВҰ218643 and the wallsВҰ218644 are completed, \add @those people\add* won'tВҰ218650 \add вүҲpay\add* \add #taxes\add*, \add or send\add* \add #tributes\add*, and \add вүҲyour royal treasury will lose out\add*.
\v 14 NowВҰ218666, because we've \add вүҲhad the favour\add* of the palaceВҰ218663, and \add вүҲbecause we don'tВҰ218667 want to see the king dishonouredВҰ218665\add*, \add вүҲthat's why we've sent this letter to update\add* the king,
\v 15 so that he can searchВҰ218679 in the \add вүҲofficial recordsВҰ218682 of the kingdom\add*. You'll discoverВҰ218685 and learnВҰ218688 that that city \add of Yerushalem\add* is a rebellious city and one that has caused harm to kingsВҰ218695 and provincesВҰ218696, and \add вүҲhas harboured rebellion there for decades past\add*вҖ”\add вүҲthat's why\add* that city was destroyed.
\v 16 We are letting the king know that if that cityВҰ218716 is \add вүҲrebuilt\add* and its wallsВҰ218719 are completed, \add вүҲthen you'll lose control of this provinceВҰ218724 on this side of the Euphrates\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 17 The kingВҰ218733 sentВҰ218732 this replyВҰ218731:
\p вҖңTo RehumВҰ218736 \add вүҲthe high commissioner\add* and ShimshaiВҰ218740 \add вүҲthe provincial secretary\add*, and the rest of theirВҰ218743 companions who live in ShomronВҰ218746 \add (SamariaВҰ218746)\add*, and the rest of \add вүҲthe people in the province west of the Euphrates\add*: Peace.
\p And now
\v 18 the letterВҰ218755 thatВҰ218756 youВҰ218757 all sentВҰ218757 to us has been carefully read aloudВҰ218760 to me.
\v 19 \add вүҲI ordered my officials to searchВҰ218766\add* \add the records\add* and discoveredВҰ218767 \add that it's true\add* that that cityВҰ218769 has been \add вүҲrebelliousВҰ218779 and seditiousВҰ218780\add* since ancient times.
\v 20 Powerful kingsВҰ218785 have \add вүҲreigned from\add* YerushalemВҰ218790 and ruledВҰ218791 the entire regionВҰ218793 that side of the riverВҰ218794, and had taxes and tributesВҰ218795 paid to them.
\v 21 \add вүҲSo command those Jews to stop rebuilding\add* the cityВҰ218808 untilВҰ218812 \add вүҲsuch time as I make\add* a decree.
\v 22 \add вүҲDon't be negligentВҰ218820 in doing that or the damageВҰ218827 to this kingdom might get worse\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 23 When King Artahshasta's letterВҰ218837 \add reached\add* RehumВҰ218845, ShimshaiВҰ218846 the \add вүҲsecretary\add*, and their companions, and was read aloudВҰ218842 to them all, theyВҰ218849 \add вүҲimmediately\add* wentВҰ218849 to YerushalemВҰ218851 and \add вүҲused forceВҰ218857 to stop\add* the Jews \add from their rebuilding\add*.
\rem /s1 Work on the Temple Begins Again; The Rebuilding Resumes
\p
\v 24 \add вүҲSo there was a period when the rebuilding of the temple in YerushalemВҰ218868 stopped\add*, andВҰ218869 itВҰ218862 \add вүҲremained paused\add* untilВҰ218871 the second yearВҰ218872 of King Dareyavesh's reignВҰ218874 in PersiaВҰ218878.\x + \xo 4:24: \xt Hag 1:1; Zech 1:1.\x*
\c 5
\s1 The temple rebuilding continues
\rem /s1 Restoration of the Temple Resumed; Tattenai's Letter to Darius
\p
\v 1 Then the prophet HaggaiВҰ218882 and Iddo'sВҰ218888 son ZekaryahВҰ218885 prophesied to the Jews in YerushalemВҰ218896 and \add вүҲacross\add* YehudahВҰ218895 in the nameВҰ218897 of Yisrael'sВҰ218899 godВҰ218898 \add вүҲwho they served\add*.\x + \xo 5:1: \xt Hag 1:1; Zech 1:1.\x*
\v 2 Then Shealtiel'sВҰ218908 son ZerubabelВҰ218905 and Yotsadak's son YeshuaВҰ218909 \add вүҲtook action\add* and beganВҰ218913 to \add вүҲrebuildВҰ218914\add* God's \add вүҲtemple\add* in YerushalemВҰ218918, and the prophetsВҰ218920 \add вүҲwho served\add* God were \add there\add* with them, supportingВҰ218925 them.\x + \xo 5:2: \xt Hag 1:12; Zech 4:6-9.\x*
\p
\v 3 At that timeВҰ218931, TattenaiВҰ218934, the governorВҰ218935 of \add вүҲthe province west of the Euphrates\add*, and Shetar-Bozenai, and theirВҰ218941 companions cameВҰ218932 to them and \add вүҲdemanded\add*, вҖңWho \add вүҲgave youВҰ218948 all permission to rebuildВҰ218952 this temple\add*?вҖқ
\v 4 \add вүҲThey also asked the Jews to tell them the namesВҰ218965 of the menВҰ218966 who were working\add* on the building.
\v 5 \add вүҲHowever, GodВҰ218974 was watching over the Jewish leaders\add*, andВҰ218973 they weren't \add actually\add* stopped. \add вүҲA reportВҰ218986 was sent\add* to \add King\add* Dareyavesh, \add вүҲthenВҰ218973 they waited for a response\add*.
\rem /s1 Tattenai's Letter to King Darius
\v 6 TattenaiВҰ219002, the governorВҰ219004 of \add вүҲthe province west of the river\add*, and Shetar-Bozenai and his companions, the \add вүҲprovincial\add* officialsВҰ219011, sent the letterВҰ218998 to King Dareyavesh \add (DariusВҰ219017)\add*вҖ”
\v 7 this is what was writtenВҰ219024 in their report:
\p вҖңTo King Dareyavesh. All peaceВҰ219028.
\v 8 Let it be knownВҰ219032 to the kingВҰ219035 that we wentВҰ219038 to the provinceВҰ219040 of YehudahВҰ219039, to the \add вүҲtemple\add* of the greatВҰ219043 GodВҰ219042, and it is being builtВҰ219045 with large stonesВҰ219046, and timberВҰ219048 is being placed in the wallsВҰ219050. This workВҰ219051 is being done \add вүҲto a high standard\add* and \add вүҲthey're making good progress\add*.
\p
\v 9 вҖңThen we askedВҰ219060 those eldersВҰ219061, вҖҳWho \add вүҲgave youВҰ219071 all permission to rebuildВҰ219075 this temple\add*?вҖҷ
\v 10 We also askedВҰ219082 them their names, so that we could writeВҰ219088 down the names of \add вүҲtheir leaders\add* to informВҰ219086 you.
\p
\v 11 вҖңThis is the answer theyВҰ219101 \add вүҲgaveВҰ219098\add* us, вҖҳWe are servantsВҰ219102 of the godВҰ219105 of the heavensВҰ219106 and earthВҰ219107, and weВҰ219100 are \add вүҲrebuildingВҰ219108 the temple\add* thatВҰ219110 was constructed and finishedВҰ219122 many yearsВҰ219116 \add вүҲago by a famous IsraeliВҰ219119\add* kingВҰ219118.
\v 12 However, because our ancestorsВҰ219129 made the godВҰ219130 of the heavensВҰ219131 angry, he let Babylonian King Nevukadnetstsar (\add NebuchadnezzarВҰ219135, \add* the Chaldean) \add вүҲdefeat them\add*, and he destroyedВҰ219143 \add вүҲthat temple\add* and caused the peopleВҰ219144 to be exiledВҰ219145 to BabylonВҰ219138.\x + \xo 5:12: \xt 2Ki 25:8-12; 2Ch 36:17-20; Jer 52:12-15.\x*
\v 13 But in the first yearВҰ219150 \add of the reign of\add* Babylonian King Koresh \add (CyrusВҰ219156)\add*, \add *he\add* made a decreeВҰ219159 to rebuildВҰ219164 this houseВҰ219160 of GodВҰ219162.\x + \xo 5:13: \xt Ezr 1:2-11.\x*
\v 14 \add вүҲWhat's more,\add* the goldВҰ219174 and silverВҰ219175 \add вүҲcontainers\add* that Nevukadnetstsar had taken out from that temple that was in YerushalemВҰ219183 and had brought to the temple in Babylon, King Koresh took them out from the temple in Babylon and they were \add вүҲhanded over\add* to the man named SheshbatstsarВҰ219199 who he'd appointedВҰ219203 as governorВҰ219202 \add over Yehudah\add*.
\v 15 \add @Koresh\add* had told him to takeВҰ219212 those containers and put them back in the temple in YerushalemВҰ219219, and \add вүҲto ensure thatВҰ219218 the temple got rebuilt in the same place where it had been before\add*.
\v 16 \add вүҲSo\add* SheshbatstsarВҰ219229 cameВҰ219231 \add here\add* and laid the foundationВҰ219233 of God's houseВҰ219236 in YerushalemВҰ219239, and since then, it's been beingВҰ219246 rebuilt but isn'tВҰ219247 finishedВҰ219248 yet.вҖҷ
\p
\v 17 \add вүҲSoВҰ219250\add* now, if it \add вүҲpleases\add* the king, let a searchВҰ219256 be made in \add the records in\add* the king's treasureВҰ219258 house there in BabylonВҰ219264, if it's \add correct\add* thatВҰ219263 a decreeВҰ219274 was set by King Koresh to rebuildВҰ219275 this house of GodВҰ219278 in YerushalemВҰ219280. ThenВҰ219250 let the king send his decisionВҰ219281 on this matter back to us.вҖқ
\c 6
\s1 The former approval is found
\rem /s1 The Decree of Darius; Emperor Cyrus' Order Is Rediscovered; Darius Approves the Rebuilding
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲSo\add* King Dareyavesh \add (DariusВҰ219291)\add* \add вүҲordered that a searchВҰ219295 be conducted\add* in \add all\add* the \add вүҲarchivesВҰ219298\add* whereВҰ219299 treasuresВҰ219300 had been depositedВҰ219301 thereВҰ219302 in BabylonВҰ219303,
\v 2 and one scrollВҰ219311 was foundВҰ219305 in the fortress at EcbatanaВҰ219306 in the provinceВҰ219310 of MediaВҰ219309, and this \add вүҲrecordВҰ219317 had been made\add*:
\p
\v 3 вҖңIn year one of Koresh the king, \add *he\add* made a decreeВҰ219327 about the house of GodВҰ219330 in YerushalemВҰ219331:
\m вҖҳLet the house be builtВҰ219333 in the \add same\add* placeВҰ219334 where sacrificesВҰ219337 were \add вүҲmade\add*. \add вүҲEstablish\add* its foundationsВҰ219339 and \add вүҲbuild it 27m high and 27m wide\add*
\v 4 with threeВҰ219353 layers of large \add #stones\add* and a layer of new timberВҰ219357. \add вүҲThatВҰ219363 shouldВҰ219364 all be paid for from the royal treasury\add*.
\v 5 Also, the goldВҰ219372 and silverВҰ219373 containers from the house of God thatВҰ219374 Nevukadnetstsar had taken out from the Yerushalem temple and had brought to BabylonВҰ219384, must be returned to their placesВҰ219391 in the temple in Yerushalem. \add вүҲSoВҰ219366\add* you must put them in the house of God.вҖҷ вҖқ
\s1 King Dareyavesh orders resumption of work
\rem /s1 Emperor Darius Orders the Work to Continue
\p
\v 6 \add Therefore King Dareyavesh wrote:\add* вҖңNow to Governor TattenaiВҰ219398 \add вүҲin the province west of the Euphrates\add*, Shetar-BozenaiВҰ219404, andВҰ219405 theirВҰ219405 companions, the officials who in that province:
\p \add вүҲKeep away from that place\add*.
\v 7 LeaveВҰ219417 alone the work on that house of GodВҰ219421. Let the Jewish governorВҰ219423 and eldersВҰ219425 buildВҰ219431 that \add вүҲtemple\add* in its place.
\v 8 \add вүҲSoВҰ219436 here's my decreeВҰ219438 about what shouldВҰ219461 be done for\add* those Jewish eldersВҰ219445 to build that houseВҰ219449 of GodВҰ219451: Using the king's treasuresВҰ219453 that come from the tributeВҰ219456 of that west-Euphrates province, let \add вүҲthose workers costs be regularly reimbursed\add* so that \add @the work\add* doesn't stop.
\v 9 Whatever is neededВҰ219471 (\add вүҲincluding young\add* bullsВҰ219473, or rams, or lambsВҰ219475 for burntВҰ219477 offeringsВҰ219477 to the godВҰ219479 of the heavensВҰ219480, wheatВҰ219481, salt, wine, or oil, according to the command of the priestsВҰ219487 in YerushalemВҰ219490), let it be givenВҰ219492 to them day by day (that is, without delay),
\v 10 so that theyВҰ219504 can be offeringВҰ219505 sweet-smelling sacrifices to the godВҰ219511 of the heavensВҰ219508 and praying for the lifeВҰ219510 of the kingВҰ219511 and his sonsВҰ219512.
\v 11 \add вүҲAlso I\add* decreeВҰ219516 that any man who changes this edictВҰ219523 should have a beam pulledВҰ219525 from his house, and \add after it's sharpened and\add* \add вүҲset into the ground\add*, thenВҰ219514 he should be impaledВҰ219531 on it. ThenВҰ219514 his \add entire\add* house should be made into a rubbish heap \add вүҲbecause of what he did\add*.
\v 12 May the god who has established his nameВҰ219543 thereВҰ219544 overthrowВҰ219545 any kingВҰ219548 or personВҰ219549 who \add вүҲmakes any attempt\add* to change \add this decree or\add* to destroyВҰ219555 thatВҰ219560 houseВҰ219556 of GodВҰ219540 in YerushalemВҰ219561. I, Dareyavesh, have \add вүҲmade\add* a decreeВҰ219565. Let itВҰ219567 be done diligentlyВҰ219566.вҖқ
\s1 The temple dedication
\rem /s1 The Temple Is Dedicated; The Temple's Dedication; Completion and Dedication of the Temple
\p
\v 13 Then TattenaiВҰ219571, the governorВҰ219572 of \add вүҲthe regionВҰ219573 west of the Euphrates\add*, Shetar-BozenaiВҰ219577, andВҰ219578 theirВҰ219578 companions \add вүҲworked hard to follow the instructions sentВҰ219582 by King Dareyavesh\add* \add (DariusВҰ219583)\add*.
\v 14 \add вүҲSoВҰ219589\add* the Jewish eldersВҰ219589 \add вүҲcontinued\add* building, and \add вүҲthey were encouraged\add* by the prophesying of the prophet HaggaiВҰ219594 and Iddo'sВҰ219600 son Zekaryah. \add вүҲAs a result of the decrees of the Persian kings Koresh, and Dareyavesh and Artahshasta\add*, they \add вүҲwere able to fulfil God's decree to rebuild\add* \add the temple\add*.\x + \xo 6:14: a \xt Hag 1:1; \xo b \xt Zech 1:1.\x*
\v 15 The \add rebuilt\add* \add вүҲtemple\add* was finished in \add вүҲmid-March\add* in the sixth yearВҰ219626 of King Dareyavesh's reignВҰ219629.
\p
\v 16 Then the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ219637 people\add*, the priestsВҰ219638, and the Levites, and the \add вүҲones that had returned from\add* exileВҰ219643, performed the dedicationВҰ219644 of this houseВҰ219645 of GodВҰ219647 with \add вүҲcelebrationsВҰ219634\add*.
\v 17 \add DuringВҰ219678\add* the dedicationВҰ219652, they offered a hundred bullsВҰ219657, two-hundred rams, andВҰ219651 four-hundred lambsВҰ219661, as well as twelve male goats for a sin offering for all YisraelВҰ219672 (matching the numberВҰ219676 of the tribesВҰ219677).
\v 18 ThenВҰ219680 they \add вүҲorganised\add* the priestsВҰ219681 to stand in their divisionsВҰ219682 andВҰ219680 the Levites in their sections \add вүҲto serve\add* the godВҰ219688 who \add вүҲresides\add* in YerushalemВҰ219690, according to the \add вүҲinstructions writtenВҰ219691 by\add* MoshehВҰ219693 \add (MosesВҰ219693)\add*.
\s1 The Feast of вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ of Messenger
\rem /s1 The Passover; Celebration of Passover; The Passover Celebrated
\p
\v 19 \add вүҲSo the people who'd returned from exileВҰ219699 celebrated the вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ in late April\add*.\x + \xo 6:19: \xt Exo 12:1-20.\x*
\v 20 The priests and LevitesВҰ219711 \add вүҲall had to be individually\add* purifiedВҰ219709, and they slaughteredВҰ219715 the \add вүҲlambs\add* for all the \add вүҲexilesВҰ219720\add* and for theirВҰ219721 brothersВҰ219721 the priests, and for themselves.
\v 21 \add вүҲThenВҰ219725 all the IsraelisВҰ219728 ateВҰ219725\add* \add the meal\add*вҖ”those who'd returnedВҰ219729 from the exileВҰ219730 andВҰ219725 every one who'd separatedВҰ219732 themselves from the uncleannessВҰ219733 of the nationsВҰ219734 of the land in order to search for Israel'sВҰ219741 godВҰ219740 YahwehВҰ219739.
\v 22 ThenВҰ219743 they happily enjoyed the Flat Bread Celebration for sevenВҰ219747 daysВҰ219748, because YahwehВҰ219753 had \add вүҲmade them happy\add*, andВҰ219754 had caused the Assyrian kingВҰ219756 \add вүҲto show favour to\add* them, to \add вүҲassist theirВҰ219761 workВҰ219762 rebuilding\add* the houseВҰ219763 of GodВҰ219766, the godВҰ219766 of YisraelВҰ219767.
\c 7
\s1 Ezra arrives in Yerushalem
\rem /s1 Ezra's mission to Jerusalem; Ezra Arrives in Jerusalem; Ezra Comes to Jerusalem; The Coming and Work of Ezra
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲMany years later\add* in the reignВҰ219773 of Persian King Artahshasta \add (ArtaxerxesВҰ219774)\add*, EzraВҰ219778 (son of SerayahВҰ219781, son of AzaryahВҰ219784, son of Hilkiyyah,
\v 2 son of ShallumВҰ219791, son of TsadokВҰ219794, son of AhitubВҰ219797,
\v 3 son of AmaryahВҰ219801, son of AzaryahВҰ219804, son of MerayotВҰ219807,
\v 4 son of ZerahiahВҰ219811, son of UzziВҰ219814, son of BukkiВҰ219817,
\v 5 son of Avishua, the son of Pinhas, the son of EleazarВҰ219827, the son of Aharon the head priestВҰ219831)
\v 6 was a skilledВҰ219841 \add вүҲexpert\add* in the law thatВҰ219844 Yisrael'sВҰ219849 godВҰ219848 Yahweh had givenВҰ219846 through MoshehВҰ219843 \add (MosesВҰ219843)\add*. \add вүҲWith the favour of his god Yahweh helping\add* \add @Ezra\add*, the kingВҰ219853 had grantedВҰ219850 all his requests, and he travelled from BabylonВҰ219837 \add @to Yerushalem\add*.
\v 7 \add вүҲSome IsraelisВҰ219866, including\add* some priestsВҰ219869 and LevitesВҰ219870, singersВҰ219871 and gatekeepersВҰ219872, and some templeВҰ219873 servantsВҰ219873 \add вүҲtravelled\add* to YerushalemВҰ219876 in the seventhВҰ219879 yearВҰ219877 of Artahshasta's \add вүҲreign\add*.
\v 8-9 They left Babylon on New Year's Day (in early April) andВҰ219883 \add вүҲwith God's favour\add* \add on the journey\add*, arrived in YerushalemВҰ219884 exactly four monthsВҰ219885 later
\v 10 because EzraВҰ219914 had made \add вүҲa firm resolution\add* to \add вүҲstudyВҰ219917\add* Yahweh'sВҰ219921 \add written\add* \add вүҲinstructions\add*, and to \add carefully\add* \add вүҲfollow\add* \add #them\add*, and to teachВҰ219923 \add *them\add* in YisraelВҰ219924.
\s1 King Artahshasta's letter to Ezra
\rem /s1 King Artaxerxes' Letter to Ezra; Artaxerxes' Letter to Ezra; The Letter of Artaxerxes to Ezra; The Document Which Emperor Artaxerxes Gave to Ezra
\p
\v 11 King Artahshasta \add (ArtaxerxesВҰ219936)\add* had given a letterВҰ219932 for EzraВҰ219937 the priestВҰ219938 and scribe and \add вүҲexpert\add* in Yahweh's commandsВҰ219942 and instructions \add to take with him\add*, \add вүҲsaying\add*:
\p
\v 12 Artahshasta, the kingВҰ219952 of kingsВҰ219953, to the priestВҰ219955 EzraВҰ219954, the scribeВҰ219956 of the law of the godВҰ219960 of heavensВҰ219961: Peace.
\p Now,
\v 13 \add вүҲI hereby\add* decreeВҰ219967 that anyoneВҰ219971 in my kingdomВҰ219972 from YisraelВҰ219976 (including priestsВҰ219977 and Levites) who freely offers to go to YerushalemВҰ219980 with you, may go.
\v 14 \add вүҲYouВҰ219991 are sentВҰ219994 by\add* the kingВҰ219991 and his sevenВҰ219992 counsellorsВҰ219993 to \add вүҲdetermine whether\add* \add the people of\add* YehudahВҰ219998 and YerushalemВҰ219999 \add вүҲare following\add* the law of your godВҰ220001 whichВҰ220002 \add вүҲyouВҰ219994 have a copy of\add*.
\v 15 \add вүЎYou are also\add* to take the goldВҰ220007 and silverВҰ220006 thatВҰ220008 the kingВҰ220010 and hisВҰ220017 counsellorsВҰ220011 have freelyВҰ220012 offeredВҰ220012 to the godВҰ220013 of YisraelВҰ220014 \add вүҲwho lives\add* in Jerusalem,
\v 16 along with all the goldВҰ220021 and silverВҰ220020 thatВҰ220022 youВҰ220023 \add вүҲcollect\add* all \add вүҲacross\add* BabylonВҰ220026, along with the freewillВҰ220028 \add #offerings\add* of the peopleВҰ220029 and the priestsВҰ220030 who freelyВҰ220031 give towards the houseВҰ220032 of GodВҰ220033 in YerushalemВҰ220035.
\p
\v 17 \add вүҲSo then\add* you should diligentlyВҰ220041 \add вүҲuse those funds\add* to buy bullsВҰ220045, rams, lambsВҰ220048, and \add supplies for\add* their grainВҰ220049 offerings and drinkВҰ220050 offerings, and you should offer them on the altarВҰ220055 at the your god's houseВҰ220057 in YerushalemВҰ220060.
\v 18 With \add вүҲthe remaining funds\add*, you can \add вүҲuse them for\add* whateverВҰ220062 seems goodВҰ220072 to you andВҰ220062 your brothersВҰ220069, accordingВҰ220077 to the will of your godВҰ220078.
\v 19 \add вүҲAlso, make sure that\add* you deliver all those \add gold andВҰ220081 silver\add* containers that were \add вүҲhanded over\add* to you for use in yourВҰ220088 god's houseВҰ220087 in YerushalemВҰ220092.
\v 20 \add вүҲAnythingВҰ220108 else that's\add* neededВҰ220095 for the house of your godВҰ220097 that \add вүҲyou need to supply can be providedВҰ220102\add* from the king's treasuriesВҰ220107.
\p
\v 21 And I, King Artahshasta \add вүҲmake\add* a decreeВҰ220115 for all the treasurersВҰ220117 \add вүҲin the provinceВҰ220119 west of\add* the riverВҰ220120: that you all diligentlyВҰ220134 help with everything that the priestВҰ220127 EzraВҰ220126 (the scribeВҰ220128 of the law of the godВҰ220132 of the heavensВҰ220133) asks from you allвҖ”
\v 22 up to three tonnes of silverВҰ220139, five hundred bushels of wheatВҰ220144, two thousand litres of wine and \add вүҲthe same amount\add* of olive oil, and \add вүҲas much salt as he needs\add*.
\v 23 EverythingВҰ220184 that the godВҰ220169 of the heavens decreedВҰ220168 to be done shouldВҰ220171 be done exactlyВҰ220172 \add вүҲas he specified because there's no good reason to make him angry at\add* the kingdomВҰ220183 of the king and his sons?
\v 24 \add вүҲAlso, it should be made clear\add* that there is no authorityВҰ220205 to \add вүҲextract\add* \add #taxes\add* or tributeВҰ220201 from any priestsВҰ220192 or Levites, singersВҰ220194 or the gatekeepers, the templeВҰ220196 servants or the servants of that houseВҰ220198 of GodВҰ220199.
\p
\v 25 As for you, EzraВҰ220210, \add вүҲuse the wisdomВҰ220211 that your god has given to you to\add* appointВҰ220216 magistrates andВҰ220209 judges who can judge all the peopleВҰ220226 who are in \add that provinceВҰ220228\add* beyondВҰ220228 the riverВҰ220229вҖ”everyoneВҰ220226 who know the laws of your god (plus you should teach thoseВҰ220232 who don'tВҰ220236 know \add >them\add*).
\v 26 AnyoneВҰ220253 who \add вүҲrefuses to obey\add* yourВҰ220250 god's laws andВҰ220240 the king's laws, \add вүҲshouldВҰ220256 receive swift\add* judgementВҰ220255вҖ”whetherВҰ220259 it's confiscationВҰ220266 of goods, or banishmentВҰ220262, imprisonmentВҰ220268, or \add вүҲthe deathВҰ220260 sentence\add*.вҖқ
\s1 Ezra praises Yahweh
\rem /s1 Ezra Praises the Lord; Ezra Praises God
\p
\v 27 Blessed be Yahweh, the godВҰ220273 of ourВҰ220274 fathersВҰ220274 who put it into the king's heartВҰ220278 to honourВҰ220280 Yahweh's houseВҰ220283 in YerushalemВҰ220286,
\v 28 and showed me his loyalВҰ220291 commitment in \add вүҲdealing with\add* the king and his counsellorsВҰ220294, and all the powerfulВҰ220299 officialsВҰ220297 of the king. And as for me, YahwehВҰ220304 my godВҰ220305 \add вүҲblessed me with\add* \add initiative and\add* \add вүҲthe strengthВҰ220301 to carry it out as\add* I gatheredВҰ220307 some Israeli \add вүҲleadersВҰ220309\add* to go \add вүҲto Yerushalem\add* with me.
\c 8
\s1 The returning exiles
\rem /s1 Exiles Who Returned with Ezra; Heads of Families Who Returned with Ezra; List of the Family Heads Returning With Ezra; The People Who Returned from Exile
\p
\v 1 Now theseВҰ220314 are the \add вүҲfamilyВҰ220316\add* headsВҰ220315 and theirВҰ220316 \add вүҲdescendants by number who\add* who wentВҰ220318 with me from BabylonВҰ220323 \add вүҲto Yerushalem\add* in the reignВҰ220320 of King Artahshasta \add (ArtaxerxesВҰ220321)\add*:
\rem /s1 Ezra Finds Levites for the Temple (was before v3)
\li1
\v 2 from the descendants of Pinhas: GershomВҰ220328,
\li1 from the descendants of ItamarВҰ220331: Daniyyel,
\li1 from the descendants of DavidВҰ220335: HattushВҰ220336,
\li1
\v 3 from the descendants of Shekanyah \add вүҲand\add* Far'osh: Zekaryah and a hundredВҰ220348 and fiftyВҰ220349 \add other\add* men,
\li1
\v 4 from the descendants of PahatВҰ220353-MoabВҰ220354: Zerahyah'sВҰ220358 son EliehoenaiВҰ220355 andВҰ220359 twoВҰ220360 hundredВҰ220360 \add other\add* men,
\li1
\v 5 from the descendants of Shekanyah: Yahatsiel's son andВҰ220369 threeВҰ220370 hundredВҰ220371 \add other\add* men,
\li1
\v 6 from the descendantsВҰ220375 of AdinВҰ220376: Yonatan's son Eved and fiftyВҰ220382 \add other\add* men,
\li1
\v 7 from the descendantsВҰ220386 of Eylam: Atalyah's son YeshayahВҰ220388 and seventyВҰ220393 \add other\add* men,
\li1
\v 8 from the descendantsВҰ220397 of Shefatyah: Mikael's son Zevadyah and eightyВҰ220404 \add other\add* men;
\li1
\v 9 from the descendants of Yoav: Yehiel's son Ovadyah and 218 \add other\add* men,
\li1
\v 10 from the descendantsВҰ220421 of ShelomitВҰ220422: Yosifiah'sВҰ220425 son and one hundredВҰ220427 and sixtyВҰ220428 \add other\add* men,
\li1
\v 11 from the descendantsВҰ220432 of Bevai: his son Zekaryah and twenty-eight \add other\add* men,
\li1
\v 12 from the descendantsВҰ220444 of AzgadВҰ220445: Hakkatan'sВҰ220449 son YohananВҰ220446 and one hundredВҰ220451 and tenВҰ220452 \add other\add* men,
\li1
\v 13 from the later descendantsВҰ220456 of AdonikamВҰ220457: ElifeletВҰ220461, YeielВҰ220462, and ShemayahВҰ220463, and sixtyВҰ220465 \add other\add* men,
\li1
\v 14 and from the descendantsВҰ220469 of BigvaiВҰ220470: UtaiВҰ220471 and Zakkur and seventyВҰ220475 \add other\add* men.
\s1 Ezra finds some Levites to take
\rem /s1 The Return to Jerusalem; Servants for the Temple; Ezra's Journey to Jerusalem
\p
\v 15 \add Firstly,\add* I gatheredВҰ220479 them \add вүҲnear\add* the riverВҰ220482 that goes to AhavaВҰ220486, and we campedВҰ220487 there for threeВҰ220490 daysВҰ220489. I \add вүҲinterviewed\add* the peopleВҰ220492 and the priestsВҰ220493 and \add вүҲdiscovered that we didn'tВҰ220496 have any Levites included\add* \add in the group\add*.
\v 16 \add вүҲSoВҰ220501 I summoned\add* the following leadersВҰ220511: EliezerВҰ220502, ArielВҰ220503, ShemayahВҰ220504, Elnatan, YaribВҰ220506, \add a second\add* Elnatan, NatanВҰ220508, Zekaryah, and MeshullamВҰ220510, as well as the wise men: Yoyariv and \add a third\add* Elnatan.
\v 17 I commanded them to go to Iddo, the leaderВҰ220522 at Kasifya, and I \add вүҲtold them to tell\add* Iddo and his relatives (temple servants in Kasifya) to send us \add @some Levites\add* who would \add go to Yerushalem to\add* serve in our god's \add вүҲtemple\add*.
\v 18 \add вүҲThenВҰ220544 sinceВҰ220546 we had God'sВҰ220561 favour\add*, they sent us a \add вүҲtalented\add* manВҰ220551 (from the sons of MahliВҰ220554, son of LeviВҰ220557, son of YisraelВҰ220560) and eighteenВҰ220564 of hisВҰ220563 sons and \add вүҲother relatives\add*.
\v 19 \add They also sent\add* Hashavyah and YeshayahВҰ220571 (from Merari'sВҰ220573 sons), and theirВҰ220575 relatives and sonsвҖ”some twentyВҰ220576 menвҖ”
\v 20 plus two hundredВҰ220588 and twentyВҰ220589 \add descendants of\add* LeviteВҰ220586 temple servants that \add King\add* DavidВҰ220583 and his officialsВҰ220584 had appointed for serviceвҖ”all designatedВҰ220591 by nameВҰ220592.
\s1 Ezra's fasting and praying
\rem /s1 Fasting and Prayer for Protection; Ezra Leads the People in Fasting and Prayer
\p
\v 21 ThenВҰ220594 \add right\add* thereВҰ220595 by the riverВҰ220599 AhavaВҰ220600, I proclaimedВҰ220594 a fast to humbleВҰ220601 ourselves \add вүҲin frontВҰ220602 of\add* our godВҰ220603 to \add вүҲrequest that he'd smooth the\add* way \add ahead\add* for us, and for our childrenВҰ220609, and for all our property,
\v 22 because I was ashamedВҰ220615 to request an army and horsemenВҰ220621 from the king to help us from \add вүҲpossible enemiesВҰ220623\add* on the way. \add вүҲAlso, you see,\add* we had \add previously\add* told the king, вҖңOur godВҰ220632 \add вүҲdoes\add* good to all those who \add вүҲhonour\add* him, but his might and his \add вүҲangerВҰ220640\add* are against all those who abandonВҰ220644 him.вҖқ
\v 23 \add вүҲSoВҰ220646\add* we fastedВҰ220646 and sought \add wisdom\add* from our godВҰ220648 concerning this, and he \add вүҲlistenedВҰ220652 to our requests\add*.
\s1 The gift and donations for the temple
\rem /s1 Gifts for the Temple; The Gifts for the Temple
\p
\v 24 ThenВҰ220655 I chose twelve of the leaders of the priestsВҰ220657 alongВҰ220660 with Sherevyah and Hashavyah and ten of the other Levites,
\v 25 and \add as they watched,\add* I weighedВҰ220666 out the goldВҰ220675 and silverВҰ220672, and the \add valuable\add* utensilsвҖ”the offering for the houseВҰ220680 of ourВҰ220682 godВҰ220682 that the kingВҰ220684, and his counsellorsВҰ220685 and officials, and all the \add вүҲexiled Israelis who could be contacted\add*, had offered.
\v 26 \add вүҲIt came to\add* three tonnes of goldВҰ220707, twenty-one tonnes of silver, andВҰ220692 another three tonnes of silver containers,
\v 27 as well as twentyВҰ220713 gold bowlsВҰ220711 that weighed another eight kilograms, andВҰ220711 two polished bronzeВҰ220717 containers that were as valuable as gold.
\p
\v 28 вҖңYou are sacred to Yahweh,вҖқ I told them all, вҖңand the \add вүҲcontainers and utensils\add* are sacred, and the goldВҰ220732 and silverВҰ220731 are a freewillВҰ220733 offeringВҰ220733 to Yahweh, the godВҰ220735 of yourВҰ220736 ancestorsВҰ220736.
\v 29 \add вүҲLook after them all carefully\add* untilВҰ220740 you weighВҰ220742 them out \add вүҲin frontВҰ220743\add* of the leaders of the priestsВҰ220745 and LevitesВҰ220746 and the leaders of the IsraeliВҰ220750 elders in the chambersВҰ220752 of Yahweh's houseВҰ220753 in YerushalemВҰ220751.вҖқ
\v 30 SoВҰ220756 the priestsВҰ220757 and the LevitesВҰ220758 \add вүҲaccepted\add* the \add вүҲreceipt\add* of the goldВҰ220761 and silverВҰ220760, and the containers, to take them to YerushalemВҰ220764вҖ”to the houseВҰ220765 of ourВҰ220766 godВҰ220766.
\s1 The return to Yerushalem
\rem /s1 The Return to Jerusalem
\p
\v 31 Then in mid-April, we set out from the riverВҰ220770 AhavaВҰ220771 to goВҰ220776 to YerushalemВҰ220777, and \add вүҲwe had God's favour as he kept us safe from any enemies or ambushesВҰ220786\add* on the wayВҰ220789.
\v 32 \add вүҲSoВҰ220791\add* we arrived at YerushalemВҰ220792, andВҰ220793 \add вүҲrested\add* thereВҰ220794 for threeВҰ220796 daysВҰ220795.
\v 33 On the fourthВҰ220799 dayВҰ220798, the goldВҰ220802 and silverВҰ220801 and the \add вүҲcontainers and utensils\add* were weighedВҰ220800 out in the \add вүҲtemple\add*вҖ”\add вүҲbeing handed over to\add* Uriyyah's son MeremotВҰ220809, the priestВҰ220813, and with himВҰ220814 was Pinhas's son EleazarВҰ220815 (and with them were Yeshua'sВҰ220823 son Yozavad, and Binnuy's son NoadyahВҰ220824, the LevitesВҰ220828).
\v 34 \add вүҲThey recordedВҰ220833 all the items with their weights\add*.
\p
\v 35 The \add вүҲdescendants of the former captivesВҰ220842 who had returned from\add* exileВҰ220845 offered burnt offerings to Yisrael'sВҰ220850 godВҰ220849: twelve bullsВҰ220851 for all Yisrael, 96 rams, 77 lambsВҰ220864, then twelve male goats for a sinВҰ220868 offering. The whole was \add presented as\add* a burnt offering to YahwehВҰ220873.
\v 36 They \add вүҲrelayed\add* the king's orders to the governorsВҰ220884 and officials of \add the province\add* beyond the riverВҰ220886, and so they honoured the peopleВҰ220890 and God's houseВҰ220893.
\c 9
\s1 Ezra's reaction against mixed marriages
\rem /s1 Measures against mixed marriages; Denunciation of Mixed Marriages; Ezra's Prayer About Intermarriage; Ezra Learns of Intermarriages with Non-Jews; Ezra's Prayer concerning Intermarriage
\p
\v 1 Now as soon as those things were finished, the leaders came to me, saying, вҖңThe peopleВҰ220907 of YisraelВҰ220908, and the priestsВҰ220909 and LevitesВҰ220910 haven't kept themselvesВҰ220906 separateВҰ220906 from \add вүҲthe idolatry of\add* the peoples of the landsВҰ220912: the \add #CanaanitesВҰ220914, HittitesВҰ220915, PerizzitesВҰ220916, the YebusitesВҰ220917, AmmonitesВҰ220918, Moabites, Egyptians, and the AmoritesВҰ220921\add*.
\v 2 \add вүҲInstead\add*, they've \add вүҲtakenВҰ220925 women from those peoples as wives\add* for themselves and their sonsВҰ220928, so they've \add вүҲdiluted their sacredВҰ220931 heritage with the anti-God customs of those peoples\add*. \add вүҲBut the worst is that\add* it's \add &our\add* leadersВҰ220935 and officialsВҰ220936 that have been at the forefront in this unfaithfulnessВҰ220938.вҖқ
\v 3 As soon as I heardВҰ220943 that, I tore my \add вүҲclothes\add* and pulledВҰ220953 some of the hair out of my head and beardВҰ220956, and I satВҰ220957 down appalledВҰ220958.
\v 4 \add вүҲAny others who respectfully followed Yisrael'sВҰ220967 god's instructions\add* \add and who were concerned\add* \add вүҲabout the unfaithfulnessВҰ220969 of the exilesВҰ220970, joined with me\add* and I sat there appalledВҰ220973 untilВҰ220974 \add the time of\add* the eveningВҰ220976 sacrifice.
\s1 Ezra's prayer
\rem /s1 Ezra's Prayer
\p
\v 5 \add вүҲSoВҰ220978\add* I got up from my \add position of\add* humilationВҰ220981 with my torn \add вүҲclothes\add* \add during\add* the eveningВҰ220979 sacrifice, thenВҰ220978 I \add вүҲwent\add* down on my kneesВҰ220988 andВҰ220978 spreadВҰ220989 out my palms to my godВҰ220994 YahwehВҰ220993
\v 6 and \add вүҲprayed\add*, вҖңMy godВҰ220997, I'm ashamedВҰ220998 and humiliated to raise my faceВҰ221002 to youВҰ221003, my god, because our sins have multiplied \add and risen\add* above \add вүҲour heads\add*, and our guiltВҰ221009 has \add вүҲmounted\add* up as \add вүҲhigh as the sky\add*.
\v 7 From \add back in\add* the time of our ancestorsВҰ221015 untilВҰ221019 today, \add вүҲwe've been very guiltyВҰ221017\add*, and in our \add вүҲdisobedience\add*, we ourselves, \add including\add* our kings and our priestsВҰ221026, have been \add вүҲkilled by the kings of the surrounding countries, or taken captiveВҰ221032, or been plunderedВҰ221033, or simply put to shameВҰ221034, which is the case right now\add*.
\v 8 \add вүҲButВҰ221039\add* now for a briefВҰ221040 momentВҰ221042, favourВҰ221044 has comeВҰ221043 from our god YahwehВҰ221047 \add and given\add* us remaining survivors a stake in his holy placeВҰ221056вҖ”\add yes,\add* our god \add вүҲhas cheered us up and given us a littleВҰ221063 relief from\add* our slavery.
\v 9 Because we are slavesВҰ221068, yet our god hasn't abandonedВҰ221075 us in our slavery, but he's \add вүҲused his loyalВҰ221080 commitment\add* \add to us\add* \add вүҲto influence\add* the Persian king to give to us \add вүҲbreathing space\add* to \add вүҲrebuild\add* the houseВҰ221091 of our god \add вүҲfrom\add* its ruinsВҰ221096, and to give to us a вҖҳwall \add of protection\add*вҖҷ in YerushalemВҰ221102 and \add вүҲacross\add* YehudahВҰ221101.
\p
\v 10 вҖң\add вүҲSo\add* now, our godВҰ221109, what can we sayВҰ221108 afterВҰ221110 that? We've abandonedВҰ221114 your instructions
\v 11 which you \add вүҲgave us via\add* your servantsВҰ221120, the prophetsВҰ221121, saying, вҖҳThe land that you're all entering to occupy is a land of impurity, due to the impurity of the \add вүҲcurrent inhabitants with\add* their \add вүҲevil practices\add* that have filledВҰ221136 it from \add вүҲone endВҰ221137 to the other\add* with their \add вүҲfilth\add*.
\v 12 \add вүҲSoВҰ221143\add* now, don't give your daughters to their sons \add to marry\add*, or \add вүҲvice versa\add*. And don't \add вүҲtry to make long-term peaceВҰ221157 treaties or contracts with them\add*. \add вүҲThenВҰ221143\add* you all will \add вүҲstay in power\add*, and eat the good thingsВҰ221167 of the land, and \add вүҲbe able to pass it on to your children for all their future generations\add*.вҖҷ\x + \xo 9:12: \xt Exo 34:11-16; Deu 7:1-5.\x*
\p
\v 13 вҖңYet afterВҰ221175 everythingВҰ221176 that's \add вүҲhappened to us as a result\add* our evilВҰ221181 actions and our great guiltВҰ221182 (even though you, our godВҰ221187, \add вүҲdidn't punish us as harshly as you could have\add*, and you've \add вүҲallowed us to survive as we're here now\add*),
\v 14 should we return to \add вүҲdisobeying yourВҰ221198 instructions\add* and to intermarryingВҰ221199 with those peopleВҰ221200 groups \add вүҲwith their evil practices\add*? You'd \add rightfully\add* be angryВҰ221204 \add enough\add* with us as \add вүҲto wipe us out completely without leaving any\add* remnantВҰ221211 or survivorsВҰ221212?
\v 15 YahwehВҰ221215, the godВҰ221216 of YisraelВҰ221217, you \add вүҲalways do what is rightВҰ221218\add*, because \add here\add* we are as survivors even to this dayВҰ221224. \add вүҲSo, yes, here we are standing in front of you\add* in our guiltВҰ221228, because none \add вүҲof us are innocent enough to stand in front of you because of what we've done\add*.вҖқ
\c 10
\s1 The people's acceptance of their sin
\rem /s1 The Plan for Ending Mixed Marriages; The People's Confession of Sin; The People Confess Their Sin; The People's Response
\p
\v 1 WhenВҰ221247 EzraВҰ221239 prayedВҰ221238 and confessedВҰ221240 \add like that\add*, weeping and \add вүҲbowing down low in frontВҰ221245\add* of the \add вүҲtemple\add*, an extremely \add вүҲlarge number of IsraeliВҰ221250\add* men and womenВҰ221256 and childrenВҰ221257 gatheredВҰ221248 around him \add вүҲto join in and weep aloud\add*.
\v 2 Then Yehiel's son Shekanyah (from the sonsВҰ221272 of Eylam) answered and \add вүҲadmitted\add* to EzraВҰ221276, вҖңWe ourselves have behaved unfaithfullyВҰ221278 towards ourВҰ221279 godВҰ221279 and have marriedВҰ221280 foreignВҰ221282 womenВҰ221281 from the \add other\add* peopleВҰ221283 groups in \add вүҲthis region\add*. \add вүҲBut\add* there'sВҰ221286 still hope for YisraelВҰ221289 concerning this.
\v 3 \add вүҲSoВҰ221294\add* now, let's \add вүҲmake an agreement\add* with our god to \add вүҲsendВҰ221299 all those women back, along with their childrenВҰ221303\add*, \add вүҲfollowing the advice\add* of my masterВҰ221306 and the ones who \add вүҲstrive to obey God's instructions\add*, and as per the law.
\v 4 \add вүҲSo take action because this is now in yourВҰ221316 hands, but\add* we're with youВҰ221319. \add вүҲLead stronglyВҰ221320 and make a clear decision\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 \add вүҲSo\add* EzraВҰ221325 \add вүҲtookВҰ221338 action\add* and made the leadersВҰ221329 of the priestsВҰ221330 and LevitesВҰ221331, and all YisraelВҰ221334, to \add вүҲpromise to implement this decision, and they did so\add*.
\rem /s1 Foreign Wives and Their Children Rejected
\v 6 ThenВҰ221340 EzraВҰ221341 \add вүҲleft that place thereВҰ221354 in front of the temple\add*, and he went to Yehohanan'sВҰ221349 roomВҰ221348 (Elyashiv's son) and went in. He didn'tВҰ221356 eat or drink, but \add вүҲcontinued\add* mourningВҰ221364 because of the unfaithfulnessВҰ221367 of the exilesВҰ221368.
\p
\v 7 Then \add @the leaders\add* \add вүҲsent a proclamationВҰ221372\add* throughout Yerushalem and all YehudahВҰ221373 to \add вүҲall those Jews who'd returned from captivity\add*, that \add @their men\add* should assembleВҰ221378 in Yerushalem.
\v 8 \add They were told that\add* itВҰ221391 was the decisionВҰ221388 of the leaders and eldersВҰ221390 that anyone who didn'tВҰ221383 arrive withinВҰ221386 threeВҰ221386 daysВҰ221387 would thenВҰ221381 forfeitВҰ221391 all their property and would \add вүҲno longer be considered as an Israeli\add*.
\v 9 So on the third day (in mid-December), all the men of YehudahВҰ221406 and BenyaminВҰ221407 gathered in YerushalemВҰ221409, and all the people sat in the \add вүҲcourtyard in front of the temple\add*. They were shivering because of the rain, and \add вүҲbecause of\add* \add the seriousness\add* of the matterВҰ221427.
\p
\v 10 Then the priestВҰ221433 EzraВҰ221432 stood up and \add вүҲannounced\add*, вҖңYou yourselves have actedВҰ221437 unfaithfullyВҰ221437 and have marriedВҰ221438 foreignВҰ221440 womenВҰ221439, thus addingВҰ221441 to Yisrael'sВҰ221445 guiltВҰ221444 \add in God's eyes\add*.
\v 11 Now \add вүҲhowever\add*, praiseВҰ221449 YahwehВҰ221450, the godВҰ221451 of yourВҰ221453 ancestorsВҰ221453, and do \add вүҲwhat he's commanded us\add* and separateВҰ221456 yourselves from \add the other religions of\add* the peoplesВҰ221457 in this \add вүҲregion\add*, including \add вүҲnot marrying their\add* women.вҖқ
\p
\v 12 ThenВҰ221464 all the \add вүҲgathered Israelis\add* answeredВҰ221464, вҖң\add вүҲYes, we do need to do what you've said\add*.
\v 13 However, \add вүҲit's the rainy seasonВҰ221480 now, and there's so many peopleВҰ221478 who can'tВҰ221487 standВҰ221484 outside for several days while we try to work all this out, because we've done so much wrong\add*.
\v 14 \add вүҲSo let's delegate our leadersВҰ221503 to make the decisions for all of us. Then we can arrange to meet together by cityВҰ221520 with our eldersВҰ221518 and judgesВҰ221522 to apply the decisions about our foreignВҰ221513 wives, until God's angerВҰ221526 towards us about these matters cools down\add*.
\v 15 The only ones who were against this \add plan\add* were Asahel'sВҰ221539 on Yonatan and Tikvah'sВҰ221543 son YahzeyahВҰ221540, with the supportВҰ221551 of MeshullamВҰ221548 and the LeviteВҰ221550 ShabetaiВҰ221549.
\p
\v 16 SoВҰ221553 the \add вүҲexiledВҰ221557 Israelis agreed to follow that plan\add*, and the names \add вүҲof the menВҰ221561 were written down by each clan leader who thenВҰ221553 stayed behind with\add* the priestВҰ221560 EzraВҰ221559, and \add вүҲa few days later,\add* they sat down to \add вүҲstart working through the lists\add*.
\v 17 \add вүҲSome two monthsВҰ221585 later,\add* they had finishedВҰ221576 \add вүҲconsidering all the men who had marriedВҰ221579 foreignВҰ221581 womenВҰ221580\add*.
\s1 The men married to foreigners
\rem /s1 Those Guilty of Intermarriage; The Men Who Had Foreign Wives
\rem /s3 Priests, listed by clans
\p
\v 18 Some of the priests' descendants had marriedВҰ221593 foreignВҰ221595 womenВҰ221594, i.e., the descendants of Yotsadak's son YeshuaВҰ221599 and his brothersВҰ221603, MaaseyahВҰ221604, EliezerВҰ221605, YaribВҰ221606, and GedalyahВҰ221607,
\v 19 and they \add вүҲpromised to expell\add* their wivesВҰ221612, and \add вүҲbecause of their guilt, each of them sacrificed\add* a ram from their flockВҰ221616.
\v 20 Then, \add also\add*:
\li1 From Immer'sВҰ221623 descendantsВҰ221622: HananiВҰ221624 and Zevadyah,
\li1
